posts:
Achievements in Competitive Programming by Junior Students

It is well known that students of IUT have to complete their undergraduateConsisting of 180 credits within 3 years and 10 months

But still with the amount of academic pressure current students are doing really good in competitive programming

Other than senior programmers like M Saiful Bari and Mohammad Abdullah Matin Khan juniors are also doing really good

4th semester student Shadman Protik was part of the runner up team in the last national programming contest held in Daffodil International University He also has 1750 rating point in Codeforces

Another student from 4th semester Zubayet Zaman Zico has solved 300 problems in Lightoj very recently as well as solved around 1500 programming problems in different online judges He is 3rd among Bangladeshis in Project Eular Contest at HackerRank as well as has around 1750 rating point in Codeforces

4th semester student Bakhtiar Hasan is ranked no1 in Bangladesh in Project Eular Contest at HackerRank

Another student from 4th semester Mahfuz Alam has solved 200 problems in lightoj He is also ranked no4 among Bangladeshis in Project Eular Contest at HackerRank

It is also great to inform that even first year students are doing very good Fahim Shahriar Shakkhor from first year has solved more than 1000 problems in online judges along with having 1800 rating point in Codeforces Some other students from 1st year are also doing very good

Not only that students from CSE Department are doing good in Programming even students from other departments are also doing programming Rashed Abid from 6th semester EEE has already solved near 1000 problems in different online judges

We expect that junior students will take part more in competitive programming and achieve much more glory for IUT

Narrated Abu Huraira

Like Judas of old
You lie and deceive

But I see through your eyes
And I see through your brain
Like I see through the water

And is buried in the mud

Fear to bring children

Unborn and unnamed
You aint worth the blood

You might say that I‚Äôm young
You might say I‚Äôm unlearned
But there‚Äôs one thing I know

Do you think that it could
I think you will find
When your death takes its toll
All the money you made

And I hope that you die
And your death will come soon
I will follow your casket
By the pale afternoon
And I‚Äôll watch while you‚Äôre lowered
Down to your deathbed
And I‚Äôll stand over your grave
Til I‚Äôm sure that you‚Äôre dead

posts:
For those who have been asking what resources did I use for the writing module Im providing the materials for you all here

1 Vocabulary  
    httpswwwieltsmentorcomieltsvocabulary
    httpieltslizcomvocabulary
    httpswwwieltsadvantagecomvocabulary
    httpswwwthesauruscom
2 Sentence structure and grammar                 
    httpswwwyoutubecomuserEnglishTeacherEmmavideos
    httpswwwyoutubecomuserJamesESL
    Barrons writing for the IELTS only grammar portion 
3 Sample essay and essay structures 
    httpswwwieltsmentorcomwritingsamplewritingtask2 
    httpieltssimoncomieltshelpandenglishprieltswritingtask2
  httpswwwyoutubecomchannelUCglDIsgZ9mE2oT9hsrbzFA
httpwwwieltspracticeorgband9essays 
Most importantly Cambridge consult books and Dr smart IELTS 

Task 1 
httpieltsupcomwritingieltsacademictask1html
          httpswwwyoutubecomchannelUCRSFsZwTpcm2IZKcWTOyyZg

The books mentioned above are on my google drive link httpsdrivegooglecomdrivefolders1LeecPB9C217f0ibxrRAvUzqU9JuX7Oh3

Notes  I took help from many of my seniorsjuniors and friends who previously scored well and I was under direct supervision of one of my senior brothers from cadet college took feedback from them and tried to improve my weak points
            In case of vocabularies focus more on topic related words than so called unique or uncommon or tougher words and be sure of the collocations Check the spelling mistakes Be careful in using linking words use them but not in excess and unnecessarily 
           Use relevant examples 
           Use more complex sentences with some simple and compound sentences and make sure your grammar is alright 
           Read samples read samples Read samples and practice 
          Plan the essay beforehand take minimum 57 minutes to plan and organize your thoughts note them down It will save your time 
          Revise the whole essay for at least once 

NB These are no professional advice rather sharing my experience which you might ignore

posts:
I can tell you exactly what happened here This happened in a business park located in Rye Canyon in Santa Clarita California 

During a car show that Paul was using to support his charity Reach Out Worldwide Paul and Roger The Owner of Always Evolving Performance where the event was held decided to take a spin

They left the AEP parking lot turning right onto Alta Vista Ave They then turned right onto Constellation Rd and then right again onto Kelly Johnson Pkwy where the driver began testing the limits of the Porsche

Kelly Johnson Pkwy has a small s curve and a wide sweeping right turn that turns into Hercules St Paul and Rogers speed was too fast into the curve and the cars rear end kicked out toward the driver side The driver then over corrected and the passenger side rear end kicked out to the passenger side

Sliding sideways at high speed the car hit a light pole directly on the passenger door where Paul was sitting and the car was splitwrapped around the pole The car then came to a sliding stop on a small tree where it then caught fire

You can Google Hercules St Valencia California and then select street view You can then follow the path Ive described above and see their final path and exactly what Ive narrated

Hopefully this puts the speculation to rest Today the automotive community lost two great ambassadors

Too often we tell ourselves we arent  smart enough or attractive enough or talented enough to pursue our dreams We buy into what others say about us or we put restrictions on ourselves Whats worse is that when you consider yourself unworthy you are putting limits on how God can work through you
When you give up on your dreams you put God in a box After all you are His creation He made you for a purpose Therefore your life cannot be limited any more than Gods love can be contained I have a choice You have a choice We can choose to dwell on disappointments and shortcomings We can choose to be bitter angry or sad Or when faced with hard times and hurtful people we can choose to learn from the experience and move forward taking responsibility for our own happiness As Gods child you are beautiful and precious worth more than all the diamonds in the world You and I are perfectly suited to be who we were meant to be Even still it should always be our goal to become an even better person and stretch our boundaries by dreaming big Adjustments are necessary along the way because life isnt always rosy but it is always worth living Im here to tell you that no matter what your circumstances may be as long as you are breathing you have a contribution to make

lifewithoutlimits
NickVujicic

posts:
FINANCIAL AID FOR JANUARY  MAY 2014 ALEVEL ACCOUNTING UNIT2 COURSE

Vertical Horizon is honored to announce financial aid for highest mark achiever in Accounting Unit 1 We show our gratitude by helping this students to do much better result under extensive guidance of our course instructor Tawsif Alam Khan It is our pride to provide best educational facilities to such talents without charging any fees We believe its you and those respected parents who deserve such respects from us 

FINANCIAL AID SCHEMES 
 Students achieving 300 straight will be provided with 100 financial Aid No course fees will be applied
 Students achieving 290 above will be provided with 67 financial aid 2000 BDT monthly fees
 Students achieving 280 above will be provided with 84 financial aid 2500 BDT monthly fees
 Regular Course fees 3000 BDT only Unit 2 and 6000 BDT both Unit 1  Unit 2 for other students No admission fees is applied for admission in Unit 2 batch

HOW TO APPLY FOR JANUARY 2014 BATCH
 Students applicable for financial aid have to submit financial aid form and photocopy of valid documents as proof of the marks they achieved in Unit 1 by 24 August 2013
 Current students must have all their regular fees cleared till the month of August 2013 
 Only new admission is accepted for those who deserve financial aid 30 August 2013 is the last date of admission for new students in current batch So far PLC and Share Issue chapter are completed and extra classes will be provided to new students at the end of October 2013 to cover those two chapters 
 Financial Aid will be applicable for September 2013 onwards

HOW TO APPLY FOR MAY 2014 BATCH 
 Students applicable for financial aid have to submit financial aid form and photocopy of valid documents as a proof of the marks achieved during admission 
 Last date of Registration 10 September 2013 
 Classes will start from second week of September 2013 
 Financial aid will be applicable from first day of class starting September 2013

TERMS  CONDITION FOR FINANCIAL AID 
 Students have to maintain 90 attendance 
 Students wont be allowed to join any other instructor for Alevel Accounting Unit 2 
 Students have to maintain honorable grade min 60 in all Mock Examination 
 Students must not get involved in any unethical activities during this course period
 Dept Administration holds the complete right to redeem financial aid for violating the above terms and conditions

For further details contact dept administration  Tawsif Alam Khan  88 01729292952 or Fahim Uz Zaman  88 01688942000

Regards VH ACCOUNTING DEPT

Always look up to you regardless of how tall I grow 

Love you more than I show

Happy Mothers Day Ammu Tomake cchaara jibon bhaaba jay na

With loads of love
Your favourite child

posts:
Dear parents of children applying to universities here particularly ones that test you on the HSC syllabus this is just a gentle reminder

It is NOT OKAY to belittle your children because they couldnt get in to a presumably excellent institution for their undergrad Especially if they like myself are coming from an entirely different academic background It is NOT OKAY to tell your children that they are useless if they couldnt get in while a few of their friends could 

Let us consider a simple example Suppose youre an ENT specialist And now youre given 3 months to learn about the heart entirely and enough to be able to successfully perform an openheart surgery whilst in a flight above Ukraine with guns on the ground ready to fire at you You may be able to pull it off but if you arent can you really be blamed 

Dont blame us for not surviving a war that we werent taught to fight to begin with Some of us get lucky Some of us dont But we all try At least the few Ive talked to who are in the same crap as myself With all due respect appreciate our efforts as much as you ask us to appreciate yours

Peace

üëè Year Review üëè

Ah 2017  the sequel to 2016 that nobody asked for The first half went by pretty smoothly but the second half was pretty rough and culminated in one of the worst things Ive ever experienced However I was determined not to let it change me and December 2017 was arguably one of the best months in my life thanks to some very special people whom I will be grateful to forever

This was the year I reconnected with old friends made new ones lost some and found out which ones really matter This was also the year where I somehow made a comeback academically despite all the shit I had going on

I dont really believe in resolutions but if I had to have one itd be to go into 2018 with a more positive outlook on life Do I have regrets Of course I do  I mean who doesnt But theyre a part of what makes me who I am today and if I could do it all again I wouldnt change a thing

pls dont suck 2018

posts:
People give it a read üëáüèª

Regarding the matter of posts disappearing from peoples timelines and people noticing unusual activities in their facebook accounts including logins from unidentified devices as suggested in the photo attached

A Facebook account normally is attached to a cell phone number and government has access to all telecom number in Bangladesh Now Government Intelligence agency DGFI and NSI can access all the telecom and they are using masking technology to access the phones text message By using the option of Forget My Password  Send a Text to Reset Password  They are changing password getting into account and deleting stuff Later they keeping all active session on so that facebook user can log into hisher account without using password as they dont want to get caught by facebook

How to fix this problem

1 Take off your phone number from facebook SettingsMobileRemove
2 Use only Gmail or Hotmail email address in recovery option
3 Download Google Voice app on your cell phone and Create a new virtual number and then use it as a recovery option Bangladesh Government has no access to Google data
4 At the end Change your password and logout from all active session SettingsSecurity and LoginChange PasswordLog out of all sessions

Make sure you take off your cell phone number from your email address as well Twostep verification is not safe for Bangladesh
Please copy and paste to share

 Information collected

posts:
All night the wind swept over the house And through our dream Swirling the snow up through the pines Ruffling the white icecapped clapboards Rattling the windows Rustling around and below our bed So that we rode Over wild water In a white ship breasting the waves We rode through the night On green marbled Water and halfwaking watched The white eroded peaks of icebergs Sail past our windows Rode out the night in that north country And awoke the house buried in snow Perched on a Chill promontory a Giants tooth In the mouth of the cold valley Its white tongue looped frozen around us The trunks of tall birches Revealing the rib cage of a whale Stranded by a still stream And saw through the motionless baleen of their branches As if through time Light that shone On a landscape of ivory A harbor of bone 
courtesy
¬•William Jay Smith¬•

posts:
On July 072015 I received a text saying my migration to Adamjee Cantonment College was successful I was neither happy nor sad about the news On July 262015 I attended my first class at the college And now Im here standing in my college campus and wondering how time flew away Leaving Chittagong and coming to Dhaka for studying was one of the saddest things for me at that time I never thought of getting such mentors teachers friends and most of all memories out of my college life back then This was probably two of my best years in this small life I have already lived 
Adamjee Cantonment College gave me the opportunity to see a leader like Tameem Ahmed Chowdhury sir I will always remember this man for making the college a whole lot better and enjoyable place for us the Adamjeeans 
Adamjee Cantonment College gave me teachers like Zakia Sultana maam to whom I can look upto for every problem I face 
Adamjee Cantonment College gave me the opportunity to spend times with so many wonderful people whom I call my FRIENDS 
Adamjee Cantonment College gave me some awesome seniors who will always be ready to help their juniors with whatever they can
Adamjee Cantonment College gave me so many memories that I will cherish throughout my life
Adamjee Cantonment College gave me a family which people know as a club Adamjee Cantonment College Photography Club  ACCPC is my family 3 I will miss working 
Last but not least Adamjee Cantonment College gave me a motto to follow and make world a better place I pray and intend to build my life based on the motto EDUCATION DISCIPLINE MORALITY
proudtobeanadamjeean 
Muhtasim Ornob 
ID  150556
Signing Out

Its been almost a year since admission period ended

Almost a year that I got into an engineering university

Trying to find my way in ittrying to learn my strengths trying to improve in my studies and also failing for the past decade or so

But it feels worse when till this day i have to hear that why i didnt make it to a particular university and why i have to study in a private one

But the worst part is after the rollercoaster weekdays when you try to rejuvenate yourself  from those bad and shitty schedules then you have to listen that you deteriorated in every aspect just because you didnt make it to that university and you gotta hear it from those people who matter to you and for that reason you donot have a opinion for your life

Ps Sorry if i couldnt convey my point
  
Obviously those people who are studying in my desired unis are worthier than mei mean THAT is why they are therebut the point isyou dont dig anyones weaknesses and show them to it everytime
It drains their motives and topples their mojos
Oh btw I tried to work my ass off to get their and you already know i didnt make it
So yeah looser
Thats all
